Design Principles

1. Unity MVC Pattern Unity naturally follows Model-View-Controller:
Â¢ Model: ScriptableObjects and data classes
e View: GameObjects, UI, visual representation

Â¢ Controller: MonoBehaviour scripts managing logic

2. Separation of Concerns

Â¢ Game logic separate from presentation
e Data separate from behavior

e Systems communicate through well-defined interfaces

3. Designer-Friendly Architecture

e All balance values in Inspector-editable ScriptableObjects
Â¢ UnityEvents for designer-controlled behaviors

Â¢ No code changes required for balance tweaks

4. Testability

Â¢ Pure C# classes for game logic (testable without Unity)
e Manager classes with clear responsibilities

Â¢ Serializable game state for testing specific scenarios

